<div class="xar-mod-head">
  <span class="xar-mod-title">
    <xar:mlstring>Blogger API Administration</xar:mlstring>
  </span>
</div>

<div class="xar-mod-body">
  <h2><xar:mlstring>Overview</xar:mlstring></h2>
  <div style="padding: 1px;" class="xar-norm-outline">
    <div style="float:right;padding:10px;">
      <img src="modules/base/xarimages/admin_generic.gif" alt="official icon" width="96" height="96" />
    </div>
             
    <div style="margin-left: 1em; margin-right: 1em; text-align:left;">
      <h3><xar:mlstring>What is it?</xar:mlstring></h3>
    		
	    <p>
			  <xar:mlstring>The Blogger API is a XML-RPC API used for blogging. The API is very simple and is 
			  basically a way to exchange strings between xmlrpc clients and servers.</xar:mlstring>
			</p>
			<p><xar:mlstring>In Xaraya the xmlrpcserver module is responsible for providing the xmlrpc transport
			  needed for the Blogger API functionality. This module will not function without
			  that module activated.</xar:mlstring>
			</p>
      <p>
        <xar:mlstring>In addition to that, the xmlrpcserver module needs one or more API modules
        activated to actually do anything. The bloggerAPI is one such module. It is advised that the
        xmlrpcsystemAPI module is also activated.</xar:mlstring>
      </p>
			<p>
			  <xar:mlstring>You can find the specification of the Blogger API at</xar:mlstring>
			  <a href="http://plant.blogger.com/api/index.html">http://plant.blogger.com/api/index.html</a>
			</p>

			<h3><xar:mlstring>Little survival guide for using Blogging tools with Xaraya</xar:mlstring></h3>
			<p>
			  <xar:mlstring>Make sure you have enabled the following modules</xar:mlstring>:
			</p>
			<ul>
			  <li><xar:mlstring>XmlRpcServer</xar:mlstring></li>
			  <li><xar:mlstring>Categories</xar:mlstring></li>
			  <li><xar:mlstring>Articles</xar:mlstring></li>
			</ul>

			<p>
			  <xar:mlstring>When these modules are activated, configure the categories modules and create some
			  categories which should hold the postings made from Blogs. While not necessary, it 
			  is advised to create a publication type for blog postings specifically and link this
			  type to the category-tree you created for blog postings.</xar:mlstring>
			</p>
			<p>
			  <xar:mlstring>Go into the config section of the BloggerAPI module and configure the publication type
			  to use for blog postings. Select either News articles or your publication type which 
			  you created.</xar:mlstring>
			</p>
			<p>
			  <xar:mlstring>Basically you're all set now to start blogging. Use your favorite tool for managing your
			  blog postings. For windows we recommend</xar:mlstring> <a href="http://www.bloggar.com">w.bloggar</a> <xar:mlstring>and
			  for other operating systems</xar:mlstring> <a href="http://mozblog.mozdev.org">The mozilla blogger</a>. 
			  <xar:mlstring>These two are the ones we test the API with and make sure that it at least works with those.</xar:mlstring>
			</p>
			<p>
			  <xar:mlstring>Point your blogging client to the url: http://www.yourxaraya.com/ws.php?type=xmlrpc and use
			  your Xaraya account for authentication. The rest should be self-explanatory.</xar:mlstring>
			</p>
		
      <h3><xar:mlstring>Included Blocks</xar:mlstring></h3>
      <p>
        <xar:mlstring>There are no included blocks.</xar:mlstring>
      </p>
        
      <h3><xar:mlstring>Included Hooks</xar:mlstring></h3>
      <p>
        <xar:mlstring>There are no included hooks.</xar:mlstring>
      </p>
    </div>
        
    <div class="xar-norm-outline xar-accent" style="text-align: center; padding: 0.5em 1em 0.5em 1em; margin-top: 5px;">
      <xar:mlstring>Extended information about this module can be found here. [modules module]</xar:mlstring>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>
